    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/843.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Livingston</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Until Department receives more detailed information concerning persons composing
                    family of Charles Zamor and manner of protection requested, it cannot give
                    definite instructions. The Department’s regulations caution its officers against
                    interfering in the internal political affairs of the country in which they are
                    stationed. No government in Haiti has been recognized by the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
